[normal]Overview on the use of Consolidation Centres in the UK Construction Sector[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]There have been specific project CC’s which will be referred to in this evidence.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“T5 was planned and delivered as a logistics project first and construction project second” Shaun Cowlam, Head of Logistics
[normal],
[normal] BAA.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The headlines from the final report 
[normal](TfL
[normal] et al, Oct 
[normal]2008
[normal]) showed many improvements in reliability (97% versus 39%), efficiency and safety. The report stated that in 
[normal]the pilot study period of 2 years and involving
[normal] 4 projects totalling 80,000 
[normal]Sq m
[normal] of office space, the use of the LCCC prevent
[normal]ed 3,000 vehicles entering the Congestion Charge Z
[normal]one. 
