[normal]Biography of Submission Author[bold], Gary Sullivan OBE[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Career Summary[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Gary specialises in Construction Logistics, supply chain development and regeneration.  He has over 20 years 
[normal]of 
[normal]experience in the planning and operation of the logistics of 
[normal]complex infrastructure projects. Gary has been involved with many high profile projects with BAA, AWE, BBC, MOD and the Olympics.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In addition to developing the UK’s foremost security and logistics contractor, from a standing start, to recognised industry 
[normal]leader, Gary has served in the Parachute Regiment and worked for the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees. He was commissioned into the Engineer and Logistics Staff Corps in 2011.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Gary was awarded an OBE in Queen’s Birthday Honours List in June 2
[normal]012 for Service to Regeneration of the Thames Gateway, and in October 2012 he received an Honorary Doctorate from Anglia Ruskin University in Business Administration.  He is a published author and a UNICEF Global Guardian.
